===Etymology===
Latin and New Latin [[hippopotamus]] from Greek ''[[hippopotamos]]'' alternatively ''[[hippos potamios]]'' riverine horse from ''[[hippos]]'' + ''[[potamos]]''

===Pronunciation===
'''Hip*po-po*-ta-mus'''
*[[IPA]]: /ˌhɪpəˈpɒtəməs/
*[[SAMPA]]: /<tt>%hIp@"pQt@m@s</tt>/
*HIH-poh-POH-tah-muhs

===Noun===
'''hippopotamus''' (''plural:'' [[hippopotamuses]] or [[hippopotami]])
# A large, plant-eating African mammal that spends most of the day living in water. (Hippopotamus  [[amphibius]])

